<%# The "notify me about this filter" bell, pinned to the right of the applied
    filter chips. Shown only to logged-in users with an active filter (an empty
    filter would be an "all new events" firehose we don't offer).

    Two states, set from @notify_rule (EventsController#index):
      • a rule already exists for exactly this filter set → the bell is LIT (filled
        accent pill) and links to that rule's editor, so there's never a duplicate;
      • otherwise → an outline bell that POSTs to create the rule (push/e-mail off
        by default) and lands on the live editor.

    Icon-only: it rides the chip row's reserved height instead of adding a row, and
    its finger-sized hit area comes from padding (see .notify-filter-link). The
    accessible name lives on the aria-label since there's no visible text. %>
<% if current_user.present? && @filter.subscribable? %>
  <% if @notify_rule %>
    <%= link_to edit_notification_rule_path(@notify_rule),
          class: 'notify-filter-link active', 'aria-label': t('events.index.notify_filter_existing') do %>
      <%# Filled bell-ringing (masked SVG, accent-painted) — the "a rule already
          watches this filter" state; distinct in shape from the outline bell. %>
      <span class="notify-bell-fill" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <% end %>
  <% else %>
    <%= link_to notification_rules_path(q: @filter.queries, l: @filter.location_list,
                                        s: @filter.style_list, d: @filter.date_ranges),
          class: 'notify-filter-link', 'aria-label': t('events.index.notify_filter'),
          data: { turbo_method: :post } do %>
      <span class="ph ph-bell" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
